Mahlatse Gallens, News24Johannesburg - The SACP confirmed on Thursday that President Jacob Zuma had informed them that he intends to fire Finance Minister Pravin Gordhan. "The president informed us of his intention to effect a Cabinet reshuffle, replacing both minister and deputy minister of finance," SACP first deputy general secretary Solly Mapaila told reporters in Johannesburg.&nbsp;The SACP met ANC officials for talks on Monday.&nbsp;More to follow.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.